&nbsp;
The prize in money, equal to 10 thousand euros for each category, equates these awards, created in 1983 by the press agency EFE and the Spanish Agency for International Development Cooperation (AECID), the Pulitzer Prizes. On this occasion 293 works from 21 countries took part, with Spain and Colombia in the lead.
&nbsp;
Spanish Diego Herrera Carcedo > will receive the photography prize > for the series "Ukraine, chronicle for images of a year of war >", published in the magazine 5W.&nbsp; For Herrera Carcedo, who has extensive experience in the post-Soviet area, the award is a “moral support” to the work of freelance photographers, whose work, told EFE, aims to “move consciences” and will serve to document history, remembering that tragedies like wars should not be repeated.
