AGI - Donald Trump's desire for revenge against his opponents is the feeling that most emerges from the analysis of over 13 thousand posts that tycoon wrote in the last year and a half. This is what the researchers' analysis of Citizens for Responsibility and Ethics in Washington, an American nonprofit that monitors the attitude of politicians and asks for them.
According to the study, tycoon has repeatedly threatened to use the federal government to hunt Joe Biden, in case Trump wins the elections in November. He promised clearly twenty-five times since the beginning of 2023. But he said a lot more.
Threats also promise FBI raids, investigations, indictments, and the possibility of slapping his opponents into prison.' Trump also hoped for the possibility that the federal investigation agency and the Department of Justice put into the viewpoint Democratic senators, judges, non-governmental organizations and members of the Biden family.> "Promises - the vice president of the CRE explained, Robert Maguire - to pursue all those who according to him are his political opponents. Practically promise to use the government for its own personal purposes and to do so against anyone who is not believed to be faithful to him or who has been openly opposed." Trump launched his social platform, Truth, at the beginning of 2022 after being excluded from major social media, such as Facebook and Twitter, now become X, due to violent messages published before and after January 6, 2021, the day of the Congress assault by hundreds of trumpian supporters.
<div </div
&nbsp;
On Truth the tycoon has a much smaller audience > - on Twitter had 87 million followers, here less than 7 million - and definitely many less monthly contacts than before. On Truth, until February, five million were on average, while on TikTok were two billion and on Facebook three billion.
